<p>Use value is used to determine the relative importance of plant species. It is calculated using the use-value formula:
 <disp-formula id="FD1-plants-09-01001">
  <label>(1)</label>
  <math id="mm1">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-italic">U</mi>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-italic">V</mi>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <msubsup>
        <mstyle mathsize="140%" displaystyle="true">
         <mo>∑</mo>
        </mstyle>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mi>n</mi>
       </msubsup>
       <msub>
        <mi mathvariant="bold-italic">U</mi>
        <mi>i</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-italic">N</mi>
     </mfrac>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <mtext> </mtext>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where ‘
 <italic>UV
  <sub>i</sub>
 </italic>’ is the frequency of citations for species through all respondents and ‘Ni’ the number of respondents [
 <xref rid="B47-plants-09-01001" ref-type="bibr">47</xref>,
 <xref rid="B48-plants-09-01001" ref-type="bibr">48</xref>].
</p>
